  <data name="IntroText" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>The American Gut Project examined stool samples from over 10,000 people worldwide and found that participants who ate more than 30 different plant-based foods per week had a significantly more diverse gut microbiome than those who consumed only ten different plants. science.ORF.at

Each plant provides unique fiber and secondary plant compounds — food for different bacterial strains in your gut. The more colorful your plate, the better your gut flora.

This app helps you track your plant diversity per week — and increase it step by step. Track your first vegetable now.</value>
